Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @potatoes{450%grams} into 1cm wide slices, then chop into 1cm wide chips
(no need to peel).

Pop them onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with oil, season with @salt{} and
@pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the middle shelf until golden, ~{30-35%minutes}.
Turn halfway through.

== Garlic Mayo ==

While the chips cook, pop the @garlic cloves{2}(unpeeled) into a small piece
of #foil{} with a drizzle of @olive oil{1%tbsp} and scrunch to enclose it.

Add the garlic parcel to the chip tray and roast until soft, ~{10-12%minutes}.

Meanwhile, zest and halve the @lemon{1}.

In a #small bowl{}, combine the @breadcrumbs{25%grams}, lemon zest and
@olive oil{1%tbsp} for the crumb. Season with salt and pepper.

== Salmon ==

Season the @salmon fillets{2} with salt and pepper and sprinkle over the
@lemon & herb seasoning{1%sachet}.

Lay the fillets, skin-side down, onto a lined baking tray. Spread a third of the
@mayonnaise{64%grams} over the top of the fish and top with the breadcrumb
mixture. Press it down with a #spoon{}.

Bake on the top shelf of your oven until the crumb is golden and the fish is
cooked through, ~{10-15%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw fish. It's cooked
> when opaque in the middle.

== Salad ==

While everything cooks, trim the @baby cucumber{1}, then halve lengthways.
Thinly slice widthways.

Squeeze half the lemon juice into a large #bowl{}, then add the @sugar{½%tsp}
and @olive oil{1%tbsp} for the dressing. Season with salt and pepper.

Add the cucumber, toss to coat, then set aside.

== Assembly ==

Once the garlic has roasted and cooled, cut the end with #scissors{}, squeeze
it out of the skin and mash with a #fork{}.

Wipe out the (now empty) breadcrumb bowl and add the garlic and remaining mayo.
Add a squeeze of lemon juice, season with salt and pepper, then stir to
combine.

Cut the remaining lemon into wedges.

When everything's ready, add the @baby leaf mix{50%grams} to the dressing and
toss to coat.

Plate up the fish with the chips, salad and garlic mayo alongside.

Serve with the remaining lemon wedges for squeezing over.

Enjoy!